content:
Search Articles and External Sources on the Knowledge Tab

Use a single search to find all your resources at once.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience (not available in all orgs)

Salesforce Knowledge is available in Essentials and Unlimited Edition with Service Cloud. In other editions, it's available for an additional cost.

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To view articles:	Read on the article type
To create articles: Manage Articles and Read and Create on the article type
To edit draft articles: Manage Articles and Read and Edit on the article type
To edit published or archived articles: Manage Articles and Create, Read, and Edit on the article type
To delete a draft, published, or archived article: Manage Articles and Read, Edit, and Delete on the article type

Enter your search terms in the Search box. You can use search wildcards and operators.

Click the search icon or press Enter. Optionally, select filters to refine your search results.

Depending on the source you are searching, filter by language, data category, article status, article type, and article validation.

When All is selected, you can filter by language and data category. When Articles or My Draft is selected, you can filter by article status, language, data categories, article type, and validation status.

You can sort articles by Published Date, Best Rating, Most Viewed, Title (A to Z), and Title (Z to A).

Use the dropdown to follow, unfollow, edit, publish, and delete an article.
title: Searching Salesforce Knowledge
